  "prompt": "How much should I expect to pay for a 1-car caltrain wrap advertisement?",
  "response": "The cost of a 1-car Caltrain wrap advertisement can vary significantly based on several factors, including the duration of the campaign, the specific train lines or routes chosen, and the design and installation costs. Generally, you might expect to pay anywhere from $5,000 to $25,000 or more for a full wrap on a single train car. \n\nFor the most accurate and detailed pricing, it's best to contact Caltrain or a local advertising agency that specializes in transit advertising. They can provide you with specific rates and available options based on your advertising goals and budget.",
